name: 斯艾娜·阿古顿
name_full: 斯艾娜·阿古顿 Siena Agudong
introduction: Overview (3)Born	August 19, 2004 in Kauai, Hawaii, USABirth Name	Siena Nicole AgudongHeight	5' 2½" (1.59 m)Mini Bio (1)In 2020, Siena stars in the lead role of Reina for Disney Channel's original new movie, "Upside Down Magic", based on the New York Times' best selling books of the same name. Siena also stars as the title character role of "Nick", a street smart con artist with a secret agenda, in Netflix' original series "No Good Nick", starring alongside Sean Astin, Melissa Joan Hart, Lauren Donzis and Kalama Epstein. In early 2018, Siena starred in the lead role in Nickelodeon's series "Star Falls" as Sophia Miller, as well as the lead role, Reagan Wills, in the 2018 Feature Film produced by Warner Brothers and Nickelodeon, titled "Alex & Me", an inspirational soccer movie about a teenage girl working hard to pursue her dreams; also starring Olympic Gold medalist, Alex Morgan. Siena was born and raised in Hawai'i and began her career in early 2013, booking the recurring role of "Lulu Parker" on ABC's Texas Ranger drama, "Killer Women". She also played the recurring role of Tiffany on TVLand's "Teachers", and was a heavily recurring Guest Star known as Natlee on Nickelodeon's "Nicky, Ricky, Dicky and Dawn" and has been seen as a guest star on Disney's "Sydney to the Max"; Raven's Home and CBS's "Hawai'i Five 0". Siena has earned several Young Entertainer and Young Artist award nominations in 2015, 2016, 2017 and 2018. In the spring of 2017, Siena won her nomination and was awarded "Best Guest Starring Young Actress 12 & Under" for the Young Entertainers Awards held at Universal Studios in Los Angeles, California. In 2021, Siena will be seen in an Indie Sci Fi thriller called "Let Us In", directed by Craig Moss and a blockbuster franchise feature film yet to be announced.
